// A base-64 encoded version of a "homemade" OSTN15-Lite. This was converted from the full OSTN15 .gsb file using gdal_translate 
// with a bilinear resampling by a factor of 10 (i.e. a 10km grid), using the following command:
// gdal_translate -of NTv2 -outsize 10% 10% -r bilinear OSTN15-NTv2/OSTN15_NTv2_OSGBtoETRS.gsb OSTN15_NTv2_OSGBto_ETRS_Lite_Bilinear.gsb
// (Why do this? Because OS do not publish a .gsb version of OSTN Lite, only the raw ascii parameters. And because OSTN Lite is 20km
// and 10km is a small enough file for our uses here without quite so much simplification).
// The resulting file was encoded to base64 then pasted into this const:
export const ostn15_osgb_to_etrs_lite = ''